And I could probably rock Black's look
summary: Guys I’m so mad I had a dream where I found a new Pokemon Black and White volume in the mall and I flipped through it aND BLACK...
body:
Guys I’m so mad

I had a dream where I found a new Pokemon Black and White volume in the mall and I flipped through it aND BLACK WAS FINALLY OUT OF THE LIGHT STONE

HE ALSO LOOKED LIKE HE WAS SUFFERING A LOT IN OTHER SHOTS BUT I DIDN’T READ IT THOROUGHLY BECAUSE I WAS IN THE MALL

Now, I could technically afford this manga, but you know what else was there?? A cosplay. For Black. In a size that would most likely fit me pretty well.

And so I thought, “hey, I can probably get more mileage out of this outfit than the manga, which I can probably find online anyway,” so I was happily on my way to buy my first ever cosplay, only then stuff just?? Kept happening?? So I never actually got to buy it or even try it on???

It’s also worth mentioning that this mall was kinda creepy. It was pure white the whole way, which, even with the decorations, is still unnerving, and at some point I found that it had the bedroom of some unknown dead guy. Who, by the way, seemed pretty cool. His blankets had the gay and trans flag designs on them.

You’d think that the room of a dead person in the middle of the mall would be pretty freaky, but somehow it was one of the safest-feeling rooms in the whole mall, along with the shop where I found the manga and cosplay.

So, my dreams derail a lot, but the tragedy here is that Black isn’t out of the Light Stone, I won’t get to see the context behind his suffering, and I didn’t get to buy my cosplay.

summary: By the way, I think it’s clear who the star was in today’s episode? Hmm? Hmmmmm? Yes Megumi Hayashibara was the star, this was...
body:
By the way, I think it’s clear who the star was in today’s episode?

Hmm?

Hmmmmm?

Yes Megumi Hayashibara was the star, this was her episode, her roles got so many references and gosh she really did such a great job today as Musashi! It was better than I expected, and I expected crazyness from Musashi wanting to take the spotlight! I knew this would not be the kind of episode where Rocket Gang ruins everything, no, they actually just joined the play lol. (Well, Kojiro and Nyarth were sort of caught into it, they didn’t want to be part of it lol)

Definitely goes on the top fav episodes list, it was tons of fun. And I do believe that it’s thanks to Rocket Gang that we got the Utena reference like, universe-wise. :D It must have been Musashi who wrote that part, or Lilie and Mao improvised. Both fit lol.

Anyway, had to get this out of me. 10/10, would watch a million times again!

title: Pokemon Legendary Gauntlet
body:
Imagine this. In the next pokemon game, there would be a gauntlet of fighting EVERY LEGENDARY POKEMON from previous generations in a triple battle. The catch, you can only capture ONE Legendary. You have to defeat the other two in order to capture the one you want.

So if you were to go into a Gen 3 legendary triple battle consist of Groudon, Kyogre and Rayquaza, you will have to decide which two to kill and leave one alive for you to catch or none at all.
